      <originalsloc id="aspace_afc91748a9d4ac0c7f069de9b0f4b97a">
         <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
         <p>The entire collection can be located in the Department of Athletics, Yale University, Records Documenting Football (RU 141).   The records consist of scrapbooks, memorabilia, correspondence, coaches files and manuals, a ledger, and printed material documenting football at Yale, including George D. Vaill's "Instructions to Competitors" and a videotape of a NBC Nightly News segment concerning the 100th Yale-Harvard football game. Records of coaches Paul L. Veeder and Carm Coza are also included.   Note: Forms part of Yale Record Group 38-B (YRG 38-B), Records documenting specific sports at Yale.</p>
         <p>HM 205 only consists of Accession 2006-A-013. Scrapbooks maintained by the football team 1901-1976.   Most scrapbooks are available on microfilm. Patrons must use HM 177 instead of the originals. The years 1902-1918, 1939,1941, and 1945-1973 are not present in this accession.</p>
         <p>1901 [not microfilmed] see box 10	
Volume 19 [no scrapbook] 1939	
1974-1976 [not microfilmed] see box 14</p>  
